1 (7) A school district, intermediate school district, or public
2 school academy that suffers any direct or indirect harm as a result
3 of a violation of subsection (4) has a private cause of action for
4 injunctive relief, damages, and any other relief available against
5 the agency, political subdivision, accrediting organization, or
6 interscholastic athletic association that violated subsection (4).
7 (8) Any civil action brought as a result of a violation of
8 this section must be initiated within 2 years after the date on
9 which the violation occurred.
10 (9) As used in this section, "sex" means the biological
11 indication of male or female, as listed on an individual's original
12 birth certificate that was issued at or near the time of the
13 individual's birth.
